parameters.name: Decimal Day
parameters.description:
This column contains the decimal day corresponding to the                 
                          spacecraft event time (SCET) of the center of the 5 second                
                          averaging window. Day 1 corresponds to Jan. 1.  Averages                  
                          are non-overlapping.

parameters.name: Bx_SEL
parameters.description: X magnetic field component in the SEL coordinate system.

parameters.name: By_SEL
parameters.description: Y magnetic field component in the SEL coordinate system.

parameters.name: Bz_SEL
parameters.description: Z magnetic field component in the SEL coordinate system.

parameters.name: Bx_SSE
parameters.description: X magnetic field component in the SSE coordinate system.

parameters.name: By_SSE
parameters.description: Y magnetic field component in the SSE coordinate system.

parameters.name: Bz_SSE
parameters.description: Z magnetic field component in the SSE coordinate system.

parameters.name: B_RMS
parameters.description:
RMS deviation of the field                 
                          magnitude.  Provides an indication of field variability                   
                          for the 5 second window.

parameters.name: X_SEL
parameters.description: Spacecraft X coordinate in the SEL coordinate system.

parameters.name: Y_SEL
parameters.description: Spacecraft Y coordinate in the SEL coordinate system.

parameters.name: Z_SEL
parameters.description: Spacecraft Z coordinate in the SEL coordinate system.

parameters.name: X_SSE
parameters.description: Spacecraft X coordinate in the SSE coordinate system.

parameters.name: Y_SSE
parameters.description: Spacecraft Y coordinate in the SSE coordinate system.

parameters.name: Z_SSE
parameters.description: Spacecraft Z coordinate in the SSE coordinate system.

parameters.name: ISUN
parameters.description:
A parameter from the sunpulse file         
                          indicating whether the spacecraft is in the sun (0) or in                 
                          eclipse (1).  A value of 2 indicates that the sunpulse file               
                          was not available and the data were processed using the less              
                          accurate determination of sunpulse time in the Level 0 data               
                          file.  There may be some errors in this column, with values               
                          offset 1 and 0 interchanged.
